1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Energy and America – When Trucks Drink Gas Like Americans Drink Pepsi

2
00:00:04,001 --> 00:00:08,000
America has long been a symbol of power, freedom… and electricity consumption as if there were a nuclear reactor in every household.

3
00:00:08,001 --> 00:00:12,000
In a place where refrigerators are bigger than student apartments in Asia, and air conditioners run 24/7—even when it’s snowing outside—energy isn’t just a necessity; it’s a national identity.

4
00:00:12,001 --> 00:00:15,000
Cars? No, no—not “cars”—but four-wheeled beasts as long as two king-sized beds.

5
00:00:15,001 --> 00:00:18,000
In Europe, people drive to get to work.

6
00:00:18,001 --> 00:00:20,000
In America, some people drive just to take out the trash at the end of the driveway.

7
00:00:20,001 --> 00:00:23,000
Every time gas prices go up, Americans sigh, shake their heads… 

8
00:00:23,001 --> 00:00:25,500
then drive their F-150s to the pump and fill the tank anyway.

9
00:00:25,501 --> 00:00:28,500
The sun? The wind? Renewable energy?

10
00:00:28,501 --> 00:00:30,500
Sure, it all sounds great… in commercials.

11
00:00:30,501 --> 00:00:33,500
In reality, most of the power still comes from coal, oil, and a quiet hope that the rest of the world hasn’t noticed yet.

12
00:00:33,501 --> 00:00:36,500
And then there’s summer—also known as “blackout season”—

13
00:00:36,501 --> 00:00:39,500
when everyone turns on the A/C at once and the power grid decides to take a vacation.

14
00:00:39,501 --> 00:00:43,500
The problem isn’t that there’s not enough electricity.

15
00:00:43,501 --> 00:00:47,000
The problem is that you can’t run the hot tub, the electric stove, the hair dryer, and livestream TikTok all at the same time if you’re living in Texas in mid-July.

16
00:00:47,001 --> 00:00:50,000
America also loves to “export energy”—in the form of bombs and foreign policy.

17
00:00:50,001 --> 00:00:51,500
If your country has oil, get ready.

18
00:00:51,501 --> 00:00:53,500
If you don’t want to sell it cheap, get really ready.

19
00:00:53,501 --> 00:00:56,000
Because energy isn’t just fuel—it’s a language of diplomacy.

20
00:00:56,001 --> 00:00:59,000
And in this game of chess, the U.S. usually owns the board… and the spotlight.

21
00:00:59,001 --> 00:01:01,000
But to be fair, America has invested heavily in green tech:

22
00:01:01,001 --> 00:01:02,500
Electric cars like Tesla? Fantastic!

23
00:01:02,501 --> 00:01:04,500
Wind farms? Yes—but they take seven years to build because… the birds protested.

24
00:01:04,501 --> 00:01:07,000
Solar panels? Wonderful—except they were installed in Oregon, where the sun comes out for about two weeks a year.

25
00:01:07,001 --> 00:01:10,000
Conclusion? America leads the world—both in developing energy solutions and in using them up before anyone else can.

26
00:01:10,001 --> 00:01:13,000
Because in America, people don’t just dream the American Dream.

27
00:01:13,001 --> 00:01:15,500
They leave the lights on all night to dream it in full high definition.